Budalangi MP Rafael Wanjala has been arrested by CID officers at a Kisumu hotel. He is accused of attacking foreign affairs chief administrative secretary Ababu Namwamba and officials from the Kenya Rural Roads Authority (KERRA) and the Kenya National Highways authority (KENHA) at Thigiri Bridge, Budalangi on April 13. It's alleged that the MP threw stones at the aircraft they were travelling in when he found out that he was not invited to attend the inspection and official opening of Thigiri Bridge. The officers arrested him at Whirlprings hotel while clearing his bill. He has been booked at Kisumu Central Police Station and is currently being transferred to Kakamega. More to follow.  Click here for the latest political news  